		"description": "<p>This oil emits a faint gasoline-like odor when uncapped. When crafted, found, or purchased, each jar of Everburning Oil has [[/r 1d4 + 2]] uses. You may expend 1 use of the oil to apply it to a torch or 2 uses to fill a lantern or a lamp, providing bright light in a 15-foot radius and dim light for an additional 15 feet. &nbsp;When lit, Everburning Oil will continuously burn until extinguished, and will continue to burn even in strong winds (though it is still affected by water, such as heavy rains). If you use a torch lit with Everburning Oil as a club to make a melee weapon attack, it deals an extra 1 point of fire damage on a hit. Once the oil has been extinguished, it cannot be lit again.</p>",
